## DNS Resolution Flow

google.com  
â†’ Browser Cache  
â†’ OS Cache  
â†’ ISP DNS Resolver  
â†’ Root DNS Servers  
â†’ TLD Servers (.com)  
â†’ Authoritative Name Servers  
â†’ A / AAAA Record (IP Address)

### DNS Concepts
- Name Servers: Tell who is managing the domain
- Domain Registrar: Mediator that sells the domain  
  (has default name servers)
- Hosted Zone (AWS Route53):
  - Create hosted zone
  - Get NS records
  - Update NS records at domain provider
- TTL (Time To Live):
  - Time DNS records stay cached before next DNS request

---

## DNS Record Types

A     â†’ IPv4 address  
AAAA  â†’ IPv6 address  
CNAME â†’ Points to another domain  
MX    â†’ Mail server records  
TXT   â†’ Domain verification (SPF, DKIM, etc.)  
NS    â†’ Name servers  

