## Memory & Storage Flow

Hard Disk (ROM) â†’ RAM â†’ Applications

- Applications load into RAM
- RAM is faster than disk
- Disk is persistent storage

---

## Application â†’ Database Flow

1. Application sends connection request to DB
2. Connection is established
3. Application runs query
4. Database fetches data from disk
5. Database sends response to application
6. Connection is closed

Flow:
App â†’ DB â†’ App

---

## Application â†’ Cache â†’ Database Flow

Optimized data access flow:

App â†’ Cache  
If data exists â†’ return response  
If not exists â†’  
App â†’ DB â†’ Cache â†’ App  

Benefits:
- Faster response time
- Reduced DB load
- Improved application performance
