- Dependency file: requirements.txt

---

## Files, Inodes & Links

### Inode
- Inode is the metadata of a file
- Stores:
  - File permissions
  - Ownership
  - File size
  - Timestamps
  - Actual disk (memory) location
- File name is NOT stored in inode

---

## Symbolic Link (Symlink / Softlink)

- Acts like a shortcut pointing to the original file
- Has a DIFFERENT inode than the original file
- If original file is deleted â†’ symlink breaks
- Can point to:
  - Files
  - Directories
  - Different disks
- Commonly used to point to different versions

Create symlink:
ln -s <original-file> <symlink-file>

Example:
ln -s /etc/nginx/nginx.conf /etc/nginx-1.conf
ln -s /etc/nginx/nginx.conf /etc/nginx-2.conf

---

## Hard Link

- Acts like a copy but shares SAME inode as original
- If original file is deleted â†’ hard link still works
- Used like a backup
- Cannot be created for directories
- Cannot span across different disks

Difference summary:
- Symlink â†’ different inode, breaks if original deleted
- Hardlink â†’ same inode, works even if original deleted

---

