## Important Directories

/app            â†’ Application directory  
/opt/app        â†’ Optional application directory  

/usr/share/nginx/html â†’ Nginx web root  
/usr/bin        â†’ User binaries  
/usr/sbin       â†’ System binaries  
/usr/local/bin  â†’ Locally installed binaries  

/proc â†’ Virtual filesystem created by kernel  
- Contains running process information

---

## Memory & Storage Flow

Hard Disk â†’ RAM â†’ Programs

- Disk is persistent storage
- RAM is fast but volatile
- Swap uses disk as virtual RAM

---

## Key Differences Summary

- Symlink:
  - Different inode
  - Can link directories
  - Works across disks
  - Breaks if original deleted

- Hardlink:
  - Same inode
  - File only
  - Same disk only
  - Works even if original deleted


